<h1>E-Commerce Conceptualization – Success with Online Shops through Structured Planning</h1>
<p>Online shops are primarily known from the giants of the online industry. But smaller e-commerce ventures are equally promising with good planning and a strategic approach. With Hob by Horse at your side, your idea quickly becomes a shop concept that we then develop precisely according to your target group's requirements.</p>
</div></section>
<div class="content">
<h2>Strategic E-Commerce Conceptualization by Hob by Horse</h2>
<p>An e-commerce conceptualization is the most important step for selecting the right shop system for online shops. The key basic steps in this preparation phase are a detailed definition of the planned product range. Helpful in this regard are market and target group analysis and the time-consuming but indispensable observation of competitors in the same industry. During concept development, core functions such as navigation, order processing and support are already defined.</p>

<h2>Strategic Details of an E-Commerce Conceptualization</h2>
<p>When developing the concept for your online shop, Hob by Horse proceeds as follows for your business success:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Defining the product range:</strong> Supply chains are reviewed, the product type is assessed for e-commerce suitability, and the online presentation is planned.</li>
<li><strong>Target group, market and competitor analysis:</strong> Marketing approach and product presentation differ according to B2B or B2C target groups — by age, gender, financial circumstances and assumed interests.</li>
<li><strong>Conceptual differentiation of the online shop:</strong> Even niche products face competition in their market gap. Your e-commerce must stand out through communicated unique selling points.</li>
<li><strong>E-commerce conceptualization with business plan:</strong> Now is the time for a new business plan with the aim of realistically assessing current liquidity for future sales targets.</li>
<li><strong>Selecting the right shop system:</strong> SaaS is convenient but cost-intensive. The self-hosted shop solution (on-premise) offers more scope through additional functions and great creative freedom. Hob by Horse handles the technical implementation using Shopware 6.</li>
</ul>
<p>An equally important part of e-commerce conceptualization is planning the shop structure and defining payment and shipping options.</p>

<h2>E-Commerce Conceptualization for Online Shops in Various Industries</h2>
<p>Strong revenue growth is recorded above all in B2C sectors such as lifestyle, fashion and beauty. Careful e-commerce conceptualization is particularly worthwhile here due to the intensity of competition. The automotive industry, online shops for real estate and DIY markets are also examples of online sales with huge ranges, large market shares and strong competition.</p>

<h2>Target Group Overview with E-Commerce Conceptualization by Hob by Horse</h2>
<p>The best online shop is logically structured for your target groups, attractively designed and simple to navigate. It contains all tools for selection, order processing and support. Technically, you as the operator can continuously update it, adapt it with further developments and always align it with market conditions for B2B or B2C e-commerce.</p>
<p>Would you like to launch your online shop with the right e-commerce conceptualization? Call Hob by Horse or arrange an initial consultation by email!</p>
